.SH NAME
ralphglasses - Command-and-control TUI for parallel ralph loops


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBralphglasses [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
ralphglasses is a k9s-style TUI for managing parallel multi-LLM agent fleets.

.PP
It scans a directory tree for ralph-enabled repos (containing .ralphrc or .ralph/)
and provides a live dashboard to start, stop, monitor, and configure LLM coding loops
across Claude, Gemini, and Codex providers.

.PP
It also runs as an MCP server (ralphglasses mcp) exposing 222 tools across 30
deferred-loaded tool groups for programmatic fleet management from any
MCP-capable client.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB--debug\fP[=false]
	Enable verbose debug logging to stderr

.PP
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for ralphglasses

.PP
\fB--http-addr\fP=""
	Enable health endpoints on this address (e.g. :9090, disabled by default)

.PP
\fB--log-format\fP="json"
	Log format (json, text)

.PP
\fB--log-level\fP="info"
	Log level (debug, info, warn, error)

.PP
\fB--notify\fP[=false]
	Enable desktop notifications for critical alerts

.PP
\fB--scan-path\fP="~/hairglasses-studio"
	Root directory to scan for ralph-enabled repos

.PP
\fB--scan-timeout\fP="30s"
	Timeout for repository scanning (e.g. 30s, 1m)

.PP
\fB--theme\fP="k9s"
	Color theme (k9s, dracula, gruvbox, nord, or path to YAML)

.PP
\fB--web-addr\fP=""
	Enable web UI on this address (e.g. :8080, disabled by default). Set RALPHGLASSES_WEB_TOKEN for auth.


